:: Event - Raider prisoner - check [Place]
<<if setup.percentageChance(40)>>
	<<goto 'Event - Raider prisoner'>>
<<else>>
	<<goto 'Wood cabin'>>
<</if>>

:: Event - Raider prisoner [Place]
<h1 class="ptitle"><<cabinName>></h1>
<br />

<<set _rpFemale = randomInteger(0, 1) === 1>>
<<if _rpFemale>>
	<<newgirl>>
	<<set _rpNpc = clone($tmpGirl)>>
	<<set _rpNpc.name = either('Scar', 'Vex', 'Brin', 'Kass', 'Dara', 'Mace', 'Lex', 'Crow')>>
	<<unset $tmpGirl>>
<<else>>
	<<newguy>>
	<<set _rpNpc = clone($tmpGuy)>>
	<<set _rpNpc.name = either('Grim', 'Bolt', 'Rook', 'Cutter', 'Ash', 'Dex', 'Scratch', 'Vest')>>
	<<unset $tmpGuy>>
<</if>>
<<set _rpNpc.origin = 'Raider'>>
<<set _rpHostiles = setup.settlements.getAll().filter(function(s) { return s.discovered && !s.destroyed && setup.settlements.isHostile(s); })>>
<<set _rpS = _rpHostiles.length ? _rpHostiles[randomInteger(0, _rpHostiles.length - 1)] : null>>

<center>
	<<image 'places/cabin/raider_prisoner.jpg'>>
</center>
<br />

When the dust settled you found <<= _rpNpc.name >> still breathing — barely. <<= _rpFemale ? 'She' : 'He'>> hadn't run when the others did. Whether that was loyalty or just bad luck you couldn't tell. You zip-tied <<= _rpFemale ? 'her' : 'his'>> wrists and dragged <<= _rpFemale ? 'her' : 'him'>> inside.
<br /><br />

<<if _rpFemale>>
	<<sayNpc _rpNpc>>
		Go ahead. Do what you're going to do.
	<</sayNpc>>
<<else>>
	<<sayNpc _rpNpc>>
		You won. What do you want from me?
	<</sayNpc>>
<</if>>
<br />

<div id="rp_choices">

<div id="rp_interrogate">
<<set _rpInterLabel = 'Interrogate ' + _rpNpc.name>>
<<linkreplace _rpInterLabel>>
	<<run $('#rp_ransom, #rp_recruit, #rp_execute').hide()>>
	<<if _rpS>>
		<<run setup.settlements.modifyRelationship(_rpS, -5, 'Prisoner gave intel under interrogation')>>
		<<run setup.settlements.save(setup.settlements.getAll())>>
	<</if>>
	<<addmins 60>>
	<<= _rpNpc.name >> didn't hold out long. Fear does that to people.
	<br /><br />
	<<if _rpS>>
		<<sayNpc _rpNpc>>
			We were sent from <<= _rpS.name >>. They've been watching your place for weeks. <<= setup.settlements.getDefenseStrength(_rpS) > 200 ? 'They\'ve got serious numbers. Walls, guards, the works.' : 'They\'re not as strong as they pretend.'>>
		<</sayNpc>>
		<br />
		<span style="color: #e09855; font-size: 0.88em;">Intel: <<= _rpS.name >> — relationship <<= _rpS.relationship >>, defense strength <<= setup.settlements.getDefenseStrength(_rpS)>>.</span>
	<<else>>
		<<sayNpc _rpNpc>>
			We work alone. No settlement. No boss. Just us.
		<</sayNpc>>
		<br />
		<span style="color: #888; font-size: 0.88em;">No useful intel — they weren't connected to any known group.</span>
	<</if>>
	<br /><br />
	<<if _rpFemale && (_rpNpc.likesGuys ?? true)>>
		<div id="rp_sex">
		<<set _rpSexLabel = 'Take it further'>>
		<<linkreplace _rpSexLabel>>
			<<run $('#rp_sex, #rp_after_interrogate').hide()>>
			<<horny_reset>>
			<<addmins 30>>
			She read what you were thinking. Her jaw tightened but she didn't pull back — there wasn't anywhere to go.
			<br /><br />
			You grabbed her by the throat — not hard, just a reminder — and kissed her. She bit your lip. You pulled back, tasted blood, and smiled.
			<br /><br />
						<center>
				<<image 'places/cabin/raider_prisoner_sex.jpg'>>
			</center>
			<br />
			You bent her over a workbench and fucked her hard, her tied hands braced against the surface. She made noise — couldn't help it. When you finished inside her she swore at you in two languages.
			<br /><br />
			<<set _rpPreg = setup.pregnancyChance(_rpNpc)>>
			<<if _rpPreg>>
				<<set _rpNpc.pregnant = 1>>
				<<set _rpNpc.pregnantDay = $game.day>>
				<<set _rpNpc.pregnantBy = 'player'>>
			<</if>>
			<span style="color: #888;">She told you everything after that anyway.</span>
			<br /><br />
			<<link 'Decide what to do with them'>><<goto 'Wood cabin'>><</link>>
		<</linkreplace>>
		</div>
	<</if>>
	<div id="rp_after_interrogate">
	<<link 'Decide what to do with them' 'Wood cabin'>><</link>>
	</div>
<</linkreplace>>
</div>

<<if _rpS>>
<div id="rp_ransom">
<<set _rpRansomLabel = 'Send word to ' + _rpS.name + ' — ransom (150 caps)'>>
<<linkreplace _rpRansomLabel>>
	<<run $('#rp_interrogate, #rp_recruit, #rp_execute').hide()>>
	<<run setup.settlements.modifyRelationship(_rpS, 8, 'Returned prisoner instead of executing')>>
	<<run setup.settlements.save(setup.settlements.getAll())>>
	<<set $player.money += 150>>
	<<addmins 90>>
	A runner came back by nightfall with a leather pouch. 150 caps. They didn't say thank you — but they didn't attack again that week either.
	<br /><br />
	<span style="color: #55cc88;">+150 caps. <<= _rpS.name >> relationship improved slightly.</span>
	<br /><br />
	<<link 'Continue'>><<goto 'Wood cabin'>><</link>>
<</linkreplace>>
</div>
<</if>>

<div id="rp_recruit">
<<set _rpRecruitLabel = 'Offer ' + _rpNpc.name + ' a place here'>>
<<linkreplace _rpRecruitLabel>>
	<<run $('#rp_interrogate, #rp_ransom, #rp_execute').hide()>>
	<<addmins 30>>
	<<if _rpFemale>>
		<<set $tmpGirl = _rpNpc>>
		<<run $guests.push($tmpGirl)>>
		<<unset $tmpGirl>>
	<<else>>
		<<set $tmpGuy = _rpNpc>>
		<<run $guests.push($tmpGuy)>>
		<<unset $tmpGuy>>
	<</if>>
	You cut the zip ties. <<= _rpNpc.name >> rubbed <<= _rpFemale ? 'her' : 'his'>> wrists and looked around the compound for a long moment.
	<br /><br />
	<<sayNpc _rpNpc>>
		Don't expect me to say I'm grateful.
	<</sayNpc>>
	<br />
	<<= _rpNpc.name >> joined your people.
	<br /><br />
	<<link 'Continue'>><<goto 'Wood cabin'>><</link>>
<</linkreplace>>
</div>

<div id="rp_execute">
<<set _rpExecLabel = 'Execute ' + _rpNpc.name>>
<<linkreplace _rpExecLabel>>
	<<run $('#rp_interrogate, #rp_ransom, #rp_recruit').hide()>>
	<<addmins 15>>
	Quick and without ceremony. You left <<= _rpFemale ? 'her' : 'him'>> outside the gate as a message.
	<br /><br />
	<<link 'Continue'>><<goto 'Wood cabin'>><</link>>
<</linkreplace>>
</div>

</div>
